OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FArctic heat record is like 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FMediterranean, says UN     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The highest temperature ever recorded  
OL,6, in the Arctic, 38C (100F), has been    
OL,7, officially confirmed, sounding "alarm  
OL,8, bells" over Earth's changing climate.  
OL,10,FThe World Meteorological Organization  
OL,11,F(WMO) on Tuesday verified the record,  
OL,12,Freported in the Siberian town of       
OL,13,FVerkhoyansk on 20 June last year.      
OL,15,FThe temperature was 18C higher than the
OL,16,Farea's average daily maximum for June. 
OL,18,FThe WMO, a UN agency, said the extreme 
OL,19,Fheat was "more befitting the           
OL,20,FMediterranean than the Arctic".        
